## Ansible

{% if ansible_kind == 'collection' %}An Ansible **collection** (`{{ ansible_namespace }}.{{ ansible_name }}`) — `galaxy.yml` + bundled `roles/`, testable with Molecule and publishable to Ansible Galaxy.
{% elif ansible_kind == 'role' %}An Ansible **role** (`{{ ansible_namespace }}.{{ ansible_name }}`) — `tasks/`/`defaults/`/`handlers/` + `meta/`, testable with Molecule and publishable to Ansible Galaxy.
{% else %}An Ansible **playbook project** — `ansible.cfg` + `inventory/` + `playbooks/`. Operational, not published.
{% endif %}
Galaxy content dependencies live in `requirements.yml` (installed via `ansible-galaxy install`).
Linting is **ansible-lint** (it runs `--syntax-check` internally) via the prek gate — no
`pyproject.toml`/venv needed.

```bash
uvx --from ansible-core ansible-galaxy install -r requirements.yml   # Galaxy content deps
uvx prek@0.4.8 run ansible-lint --all-files                          # lint (also in the gate)
{% if ansible_role_based -%}
uvx --from molecule --with 'molecule-plugins[docker]' molecule test  # converge + verify (needs Docker)
{% endif -%}
{% if ansible_kind == 'playbooks' -%}
ansible-playbook playbooks/site.yml                                  # run the play
{% endif -%}
```
{% if publish_to_galaxy %}
Published to **[Ansible Galaxy](https://galaxy.ansible.com)** on each GitHub Release
(`.github/workflows/publish-galaxy.yml`). Galaxy has no OIDC trusted publishing, so set an
**`ANSIBLE_GALAXY_API_KEY`** repository secret (from your Galaxy account → Preferences → API key)
to enable it; until then the workflow fails loudly rather than silently skipping.
{% endif %}{% endif %}{% if publish_to_pypi %}
## Publishing to PyPI

Published to **[PyPI](https://pypi.org/project/{{ project_slug }}/)** on each GitHub Release
(`.github/workflows/publish.yml`), dress-rehearsed through **TestPyPI** first — build once,
publish to TestPyPI, install and import the built wheel, then (gated on that) publish to
PyPI. Auth is OIDC **Trusted Publishing** (no long-lived secret), bound to two GitHub
**deployment environments** — `testpypi` and `pypi` — each restricted to `v*` tag
deployments.

One-time setup before the first release:

1. Create the `testpypi` and `pypi` environments (repo Settings → Environments), each with
   a deployment branch/tag policy restricted to `v*` tags.
2. Add a pending Trusted Publisher on [test.pypi.org](https://test.pypi.org/manage/account/publishing/)
   and [pypi.org](https://pypi.org/manage/account/publishing/), each pointing at owner
   `{{ repo_owner }}`, repo `{{ repo_name }}`, workflow `publish.yml`, and the matching
   environment (`testpypi` / `pypi`).

Until both publishers exist, `uv publish` fails loudly rather than silently skipping.
